A former New York financier found guilty of earning almost a million dollars from insider trading, who famously bolted from a press pack and lost his flip-flops, is hoping to become a North Dakota truck driver.

Michael Lucarelli, 52, pleaded guilty to a federal securities fraud charge last September and now hopes to begin a new life on the open road, driving trucks, it's been reported.

It's understood that he is working towards earning a truck driver's licence while living in North Dakota with his brother.

However, he may not realise his dream as he faces several years in jail and may have to pay back almost $900,000 that he obtained fraudulently.

