A sentencing memo said he expects 'to be licensed and to drive tractor trailers', according to the New York Daily News.

It also said he 'will never again trade another stock or work in any stock related field'.

Mr Lucarelli was ridiculed last August when he ran from media waiting for him outside a court in New York following a hearing for his case.

He ran out of his sandals racing down the sidewalk in a tank top and slacks, earning him a mocking 'Moment of Zen' on The Daily Show With Jon Stewart.

In a September hearing he described his crime to U.S. District Judge Jesse M. Furman, Lucarelli apologized and paused briefly to cry.

